pr_body:
As explained here: https://github.com/pytorch/ignite/wiki/Roadmap#refactor-engine
This PR will separate the events registration code from the other code.

Check list:

- [x] New tests are added (if a new feature is added)
- [x] New doc strings: description and/or example code are in RST format
- [x] Documentation is updated (if required)


Code adapted from https://github.com/vfdev-5/ignite/tree/eventdriven

pr_body:
The second PR to tackle refactoring the Engine: https://github.com/pytorch/ignite/wiki/Roadmap#refactor-engine

In this PR we move state from `ignite.engine.events.State` to `ignite.engine.state.State` 

Check list:

- [ ] New tests are added (if a new feature is added)
- [ ] New doc strings: description and/or example code are in RST format
- [x] Documentation is updated (if required)
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 671696071, 'comment_body': "To keep BC-compatibility, let's try to import State here as well and revert `__all__`", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 17, 13, 13, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vfdev-5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 671698486, 'comment_body': "I am not sure if we can import state here, importing State here will give this
```
ImportError: cannot import name 'CallableEventWithFilter' from partially initialized module 'ignite.engine.events' (most likely due to a circular import) 
```", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 17, 13, 35, 39, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'KickItLikeShika', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 671698792, 'comment_body': 'I think it is possible to do that by checking carefully what we need to import in state.py', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 17, 13, 38, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vfdev-5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 671716784, 'comment_body': 'We are using `CallableEventWithFilter` for type checking, but using `Events` is important here, so importing it is a must, what do you think?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 17, 16, 29, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'KickItLikeShika', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 671740645, 'comment_body': "Yes, that's correct about `CallableEventWithFilter` and `Events`. There is still a solution to solve this circular import issue, it is not very elegant but it would help to keep BC and seems like isort wont complaint.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 17, 20, 32, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vfdev-5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 671842183, 'comment_body': 'I think this can be resolved now, thanks for proposing the solution!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 18, 13, 22, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'KickItLikeShika', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_body:
The third PR to tackle refactoring the Engine: https://github.com/pytorch/ignite/wiki/Roadmap#refactor-engine

In this PR we move `CallableEventWithFilter`, `EventEnum`, `EventsList`, and `RemovableEventHandle` from `ignite.engine.events` to `ignite.base.base_events`

Check list:

- [ ] New tests are added (if a new feature is added)
- [x] New doc strings: description and/or example code are in RST format
- [x] Documentation is updated (if required)
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 673863714, 'comment_body': "let's name it as `ignite.base.events`", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 21, 10, 43, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vfdev-5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673863872, 'comment_body': 'Please, no BC-breaking changes.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 21, 10, 43, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vfdev-5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673910774, 'comment_body': 'Reverted this, thanks!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 21, 12, 3, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'KickItLikeShika', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 674015077, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
Base module for Ignite Engine, Events and State.
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 21, 14, 16, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vfdev-5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 674640447, 'comment_body': "Doing this as string does not look good. Let's find another solution.
How about creating `ignite.engine.events.EventEnum` as shortcut of `import ignite.base.events.EventEnum` inside  `ignite/engine/events.py`?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 22, 9, 30, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vfdev-5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 674645481, 'comment_body': 'Can you please explain your point?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 22, 9, 37, 51, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'KickItLikeShika', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 676899676, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
    The classes below are defined in :ref:`base-events` and also

    recommend importing them from :ref:`base-events`.

pr_body:
The 4th PR to tackle refactoring the Engine: https://github.com/pytorch/ignite/wiki/Roadmap#refactor-engine

In this PR we introduced new class to build custom engines called `EventsDrivenWithState` + docs + tests. Also made some updates in `EventsDriven` and `EventsDrivenState` + Introduced `attr_to_events` in `State`

Check list:

- [x] New tests are added (if a new feature is added)
- [x] New doc strings: description and/or example code are in RST format
- [x] Documentation is updated (if required)
